# TRU Examples

## Quick Start

```python
from tru import TRU, verify

# Quick verify
verdict = verify("NVIDIA has achieved AGI")
print(verdict.verdict)  # INSUFFICIENT_EVIDENCE

# Full client
tru = TRU()
stats = tru.stats()
print(f"{stats.total_cached} primaries loaded")
```

## Example 1: Check AI Claims

```python
from tru import TRU

tru = TRU()

# Check for NVIDIA AGI claims
results = tru.search("nvidia AGI", source_type="sec")
for r in results:
    print(f"[{r.date}] {r.title}")

# Verify claim
v = tru.verify("NVIDIA announced AGI in 2025")
print(f"Verdict: {v.verdict}")
print(f"Evidence: {v.evidence_count} sources")
```

## Example 2: Temple Institute Research

```python
from tru import TRU

tru = TRU()

# Search temple posts
results = tru.search("red heifer", source_type="temple")
for r in results:
